  "text": "Another shortcoming of cosine similarity is that it only considers \"co-owning\" visual words but ignores the evidences from \"co-missing\" ones. If word c i does not appear in a probe image, the contribution of c i is zero no matter what the term frequency of c i is in gallery images. Actually a gallery image without c i is more similar with the probe and should have a higher matching score than other people containing c i . Jégou et al in [CITATION_1] raise this problem and give a simple yet effective solution in which a feature vector is transformed using equation below:",
